#: ../../source/installation.rst:2
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:3
msgid ""
"This section will guide you through the setup of Effektif. Simply follow the"
" subsections step by step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:6
msgid "System requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:9
msgid "Operating system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:10
msgid ""
"The Effektif system can be deployed on different operating systems. "
"Officially supported are the following operating systems:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:12
msgid "Debian Stable Release 64Bit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:13
msgid "Microsoft Windows Server 64Bit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:15
msgid ""
"You are advised to use a 64Bit operating system in order to be able to "
"assign more than 1.5GB of heap space to the Java VM. Furthermore, MongoDB is"
" limited to 2GB of content on 32Bit operating systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:18
msgid "Hardware requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:19
msgid ""
"The described installation in this adminstration guide will setup the "
"database and the application server on the same system. However, it is also "
"possible to setup the database and application server on separate systems. "
"For instance, if you have already an infrastructure that provides MongoDB "
"instances for different applications, you can simply reuse your "
"infrastructure and just create another database for Effektif."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:21
msgid ""
"The minimal hardware requirements for the combined system of application and"
" database server are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:23
msgid "4 GB RAM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:24
msgid "4 core CPU"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:25
msgid "50 GB disk space"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:27
msgid ""
"The mentioned amount of RAM will be sufficient to execute the Effektif "
"system. Nevertheless, if you can provide the system with more memory, you "
"are advised to do so. Especially MongoDB will benefit from additional system"
" memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:29
msgid ""
"The required disk space depends on how you will use Effektif. 50 GB should "
"be sufficient disk space for most scenarios. However, if you plan on using a"
" lot of file uploads in your processes the required disk space depends "
"largely on the number and size of the uploaded files. Be aware, the required"
" disk space does not include the space necessary for backups. If you plan on"
" storing the backups on the same server, you should add more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:32
msgid "Other systems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:33
msgid ""
"The Effektif system relies on a SMTP mail server to send notifications and "
"invite users. You can simply reuse any existing mail server in your "
"organization that supports access via SMTP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:36
msgid "Software requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:37
msgid ""
"In order to run Effektif on your server, you will need to install some "
"additional software. Depending on your deployment strategy (combined or "
"separate system for application and database), you have to install the "
"following software requirements either on the same server or the respective "
"separate servers. The next sections will contain additional instructions on "
"how to install and configure the additional software components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:39
msgid "The application server requires the following additional software:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:41
msgid "Java: Oracle JSE version 7 (1.7.0_67+)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:42
msgid "Apache Tomcat 7"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:44
msgid "The database server requires the following additional software:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:46
msgid "MongoDB version 2.4.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:48
msgid ""
"Be aware, MongoDB version 2.6.x is not yet officially supported by Effektif."
" Please, make sure to install version 2.4.x."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:51
msgid "Web browser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:52
msgid ""
"A current web browser is necessary on every client that shall display the "
"Effektif user interface. The following list shows the supported web browsers"
" and versions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:54
msgid "Google Chrome 23 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:55
msgid "Mozilla Firefox 10 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:56
msgid "Microsoft Internet Explorer 9 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:57
msgid "Apple Safari 5 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:60
msgid "Unpack Effektif"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:61
msgid ""
"Unzip the effektif-{version}.zip to a directory of your choice, e.g. "
"``/yourlocation/effektif-{version}`` In the rest of this guide, we'll refer "
"to the effektif home directory as ``$EFFEKTIF_HOME``\\ . The directory will "
"contain the following files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:65
msgid "\\*.sh - Linux shell scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:66
msgid "db - directory that contains MongoDB configuration files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:68
msgid "mongodb.conf - configuration file for Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:69
msgid "mongod.cfg - configuration file for Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:71
msgid "effektif - directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:73
msgid "ROOT - this directory contains the web application"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:75
msgid ""
"On Linux systems you need to make the scripts executable with the chmod "
"command like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:77
msgid "``chmod a+x $EFFEKTIF_HOME/*.sh``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:80
msgid "Install Java"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:81
msgid ""
"The application server requires a Java runtime environment in order to "
"execute the Java backend of Effektif. Therefore, you have to install Java 7 "
"64Bit on the application server. You can download a respective installation "
"package for your operating system here:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:83
msgid "https://www.java.com/en/download/manual.jsp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:86
msgid "Install Tomcat"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:87
msgid ""
"The Java backend of the Effektif system is executed using Apache Tomcat 7. "
"Effektif does not support any older or younger versions of Tomcat than "
"version 7."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:89
msgid ""
"You can download the latest installation files for different operating "
"systems from the following site:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:91
msgid "http://tomcat.apache.org/download-70.cgi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:93
msgid ""
"In general, please make sure the user executing the Tomcat has read / write "
"permissions for the folder ``$TOMCAT_HOME/webapps`` and the containing "
"subfolders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:96 ../../source/installation.rst:134
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:97
msgid ""
"If you are using a Windows system, the download site offers a Windows "
"Service Installer (“32-bit/64-bit Windows Service Installer”). This "
"installer will install the Apache Tomcat as a Windows service which can be "
"started, stopped and configured over a graphical user interface. The service"
" installer is the recommended way for Windows users to install the Tomcat "
"server. Please, make sure you execute the installer with administrator "
"privileges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:99
msgid ""
"Furthermore, it is recommended to install the Apache Tomcat into a root "
"folder on ``C:\\``\\ ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:102 ../../source/installation.rst:146
msgid "Debian"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:103
msgid ""
"If you are using Linux, you might consider installing Apache Tomcat using a "
"packet manager. In case of Debian, you can use the Advanced Packaging Tool "
"(APT) and execute the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:105
msgid "``apt-get install tomcat7``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:108
msgid "Configure Tomcat"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:109
msgid ""
"This section will point the configuration options that are required to run "
"Effektif. However, Tomcat offers more configuration options that can be "
"found in the official documentation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:111
msgid "http://tomcat.apache.org/tomcat-7.0-doc/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:114
msgid "Java options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:115
msgid ""
"There are some Java options that need to be configured before starting the "
"Tomcat server. These options are configured using the ``JAVA_OPTS`` "
"environment variable. It should contain the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:118
msgid "``-Xms1536m``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:118
msgid "minimum RAM, should be at least 1.5GB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:120
msgid "``-Xmx2048m``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:120
msgid "maximum RAM, should be at least 2GB but more is recommended"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:122
msgid "``-Dfile.encoding=UTF-8``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:122
msgid "sets UTF-8 as Apache Tomcats default encoding mechanism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:124
msgid "``-XXPermSize=128m``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:124
msgid "initial permanent generation space in MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:126
msgid "``-XXMaxPermSize=256m``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:126
msgid "maximum permanent generation space in MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:129
msgid ""
"In order to allocate sufficient RAM to the Tomcat server you have to set the"
" options Xms and Xmx followed by the number of MB allocated and a literal "
"‘m’. ``Xms`` defines the initial / minimum amount of RAM that is used and "
"``Xmx`` the allowed maximum. You are advised to allocate at least 2GB of RAM"
" to the Tomcat. However, it is recommended to use more RAM. For example, if "
"you want to assign 4GB of maximum RAM the option would be ``-Xmx4096m``\\ ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:131
msgid ""
"The values for the permanent generation space have to be increased as well, "
"these are defined by the values ``-XX:PermSize=128m`` and "
"``-XX:MaxPermSize=256m``\\ ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:135
msgid ""
"If you installed Tomcat using the Windows service installer, you can open "
"the configuration dialog by opening the Windows start menu and selecting "
"``Program Files\\Apache Tomcat\\Configure Tomcat``\\ ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:141
msgid "This is the Tomcat configuration dialog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:143
msgid ""
"The tab Java offers the possibility to set the options and define the memory"
" pool (minimum and maximum RAM usage). Fill in the values for Xms and Xmx "
"into the fields for memory pool and add the other options to the text area "
"labeled as Java Options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:147
msgid ""
"One way to define the ``JAVA_OPTS`` under Debian and other Linux "
"distributions is to create the file setenv.sh in the Tomcat 7 ``/bin/`` "
"directory. This directory contains also other files like the "
"``catalina.sh``\\ , the ``startup.sh`` or the ``shutdown.sh`` und is for "
"instance located in ``/usr/share/tomcat7`` or a similar directory. Simply "
"create or extend any existing setenv.sh file and add the line for ``the "
"JAVA_OPTS``\\ :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/installation.rst:150
msgid "``export JAVA_OPTS=”$JAVA_OPTS -Xms1536m [... add the other options]``"
msgstr ""
